<br>
For those asking, this is IV's admissions policy; <br>
<br>
We are currently only accepting applications from level 58 plus players.  Exceptions are being made in the case of those that applied when requirements were lower, and possibly for classes we have higher need for.<br>
<br>
You must let us know of your interest in joining by posting in our Membership Application section on our message board. Be sure to tell us about yourself, about why you want to join IV and how you think you would contribute to bettering our guild. <br>
<br>
After posting, get to know us, make friends in the guild, make a name for yourself. <br>
<br>
When we feel you are known enough and have the right attitude, we will move your application to our private section for the vote. Our recruiting officer, will create a post in our members section where members will have one week (1 week) to vote. A minimum of 25 sponsors are required to pass with no more than 5 votes against. After the 1 week period, Our recruiting officer will inform you on the outcome of the vote. <br>
<br>
1. If you do not pass the vote because you have more than 5 votes against, that usually means you have some issues to work out with a few members before being able to reapply. You will not be able to reapply for a period of 2 months.<br>
<br>
2. If you do not pass the vote because you have less than 25 sponsors *and* you have no more than 5 votes against, this usually means not enough people know you and you must continue to make friends in the guild and make yourself known to our members. You will be able to reapply in 3 weeks time. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Important Requirement<br>
<br>
We oblige all prospects to work out any problems or conflicts they may have with current Infinitus Vindicat members. Preservation of harmony between guildmates is imperative to our success and achievement of our goals. Thus, if a prospect is seen has having too many conflicts* with existing members, the prospect will not receive an invitation (even if the minimum requirements are met) until the conflicts are worked out.<br>
<br>
The &quot;MORTAL ENEMY&quot; clause <br>
<br>
If a candidate has wronged an Infinitus Vindicat member to the point where if that candidate were to join the current member would leave, that candidate cannot continue in the process. Infinitus Vindicat is building our tight family atmosphere by being, well, a tight knit family. Officers will ALWAYS side with the guild in these kinds of matters. It should be noted however that invocation of this clause requires an investigation into the situation between the candidate and the member, and is not to be used lightly. Abuse of this clause is against Infinitus Vindicat policy and carries with it heavy consequences (suspension, guild removal). <br>
<br>
Provisional Membership<br>
<br>
If the candidate has met the above criteria, then the candidate is invited to the guild by either the Admissions Officer (Maxamillian) or someone he designates. He/she will have access to our guild tag, chat, and private message board. As a provisional member, they are on a one (1) month probational term. During this probationary period the new member is required to do the following: <br>
<br>
1. Learn and follow guild policy. <br>
2. Attend scheduled raids (if they are online). <br>
3. Attend scheduled guild meetings (unless RL circumstances do not allow). <br>
4. It should be noted that the initial month of membership  is probational.  The guild leaders have the right to remove anyone during their probation period for any reason the Council deems reasonable. <br>
<br>
Failure to meet these requirements at the end of the one month term is grounds for dismissal. <br>
<br>
Communique<br>
<br>
Prospective members are NOT permitted to use the Infinitus Vindicat guild tag in any public posts during their probational period. They are also NOT permitted to post any derogatory or defaming comments about any player or guild without the express permission of the guild leader. Violation of this policy is grounds for immediate dismissal. <br>
<br>
Full Membership <br>
<br>
Full membership is granted to a new member at the end of the one month period provided they have met the above requirements. <br>
